dcterms:description: A dataset containing electronic health records (EHRs) related to chronic diseases, such as cancer, diabetes, and mental disease, used to facilitate medical diagnosis and model dynamic treatment regimes.
dcterms:title: Electronic Health Records (EHRs)

dcterms:description: A dataset of clinical cancer treatments used to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed algorithm in generating dynamic treatment regimes.
dcterms:title: Clinical cancer treatments

dcterms:creator: Y. Goldberg
M. R. Kosorok
dcterms:description: The model proposed by Goldberg and Kosorok (2012) for generating clinical trajectory data, which is used in the context of Q-learning with censored data.
dcterms:title: Clinical trajectory data model

dcterms:creator: Y. Zhao
M. R. Kosorok
D. Zeng
dcterms:description: The model proposed by Zhao et al. (2009) for simulating cancer dynamics, which is utilized in the context of reinforcement learning design for cancer clinical trials.
dcterms:title: Cancer dynamics simulation model

dcterms:creator: J. Ishigooka
M. Murasaki
S. Miura
Group TOLPIS
dcterms:description: The model proposed by Ishigooka et al. (2000) for schizophrenia treatment outcomes, which is referenced in the context of dynamic treatment regimes.
dcterms:title: Schizophrenia treatment outcomes model

dcterms:creator: R. Padmanabhan
N. Meskin
W. M. Haddad
dcterms:description: The model proposed by Padmanabhan et al. (2017) for drug dosing in cancer chemotherapy, which is relevant for reinforcement learning-based control.
dcterms:title: Drug dosing model for cancer chemotherapy

dcterms:creator: P. E. Marik
W. T. Linde-Zwirble
E. A. Bittner
J. Sahatjian
D. Hansell
dcterms:description: The model proposed by Marik et al. (2017) for fluid administration in severe sepsis, which is analyzed using a large national database.
dcterms:title: Fluid administration model in severe sepsis
